f(x) = \frac{x^2 + 3x -1}{x-1}.
f(x) = p(x)/q(x),
f' = (p'q - q'p)/q^2,
f'(x) = \frac{(2x+3)(x-1) - (1)(x^2+3x-1)}{(x-1)^2} = \frac{x^2-2x-2}{(x-1)^2}.
